  {
    "action": {
      "input": {
        "description": " A standalone operating company designed to contract with customers, issue invoices, collect payments, and host production frontends. By separating commercial activity from development entities, the RGH reduces regulatory spillover and protects core contributors and IP.\n\n**Typical use cases:**\n\n1. SaaS or protocol interfaces with paying customers\n2. Regulatory or jurisdiction\u2011specific exposure for frontends\n3. Separation of DevCo and OpCo roles\n\nSuitable for Teams that already operate a DevCo and want clearer risk, tax, or regulatory boundaries.",
        "lastModified": "2026-04-03T10:59:39.000Z",
        "summary": "A dedicated, customer-facing operating company to isolate commercial and regulatory risk from development activities.\n",
        "thumbnailUrl": "https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Ffskvmdcowx3ur8ql6utk.png",
